# 9. 見えない星

Saki: Band practice was fun! Luka joining us was a big surprise!
Ichika: Yeah. Having both her and Miku really helped us get a lot more out of that practice session, though.
Saki: For sure! Gosh, I can't wait to get better and show off to Shiho and Hona!
Saki: I can picture it now! When did they learn to play so well? I wonder if they'll still let me join...
Ichika: Hehe. Your impressions of Shiho have always been spot-on.
Saki: Thanks! Shiho denies it, but it's a fact!
Saki: Let's meet up for practice again tomorrow. Bye!
Ichika: Okay. See you tomorrow!
Ichika: (Saki makes everything fun, like back in the old days.)
Ichika: (But I keep thinking that I should tell her what happened when she was away. I just don't know how.)
Ichika: Shiho, let's have lunch together. Honami can join us today as well.
Ichika: (We were put in different classes from the second year of junior high school. I would go to their classrooms during the lunchbreak, until one day...)
Shiho: Don't talk to me anymore.
Ichika: M-Me?
Shiho: I want to eat lunch quickly so I can practice bass. Don't come over anymore.
Ichika: B-But... Shiho...
Ichika: (All of a sudden, Shiho didn't want to hang out with us. She grew more and more distant.)
Ichika: (When I asked her why, she replied that she wanted to be left alone and that was it.)
Ichika: (And then, Honami...)
Honami: Oh...
Ichika: Honami?
Ichika: Um... You bought some apple pies? Wait, is that bag ALL apple pies?
Honami: Er... Uh...
Honami: Yes... It's so embarrassing. Please don't tell anyone.
Ichika: I remember you used to get them often. So you still like them a lot.
Honami: Yes... I can't get enough.
Ichika: .....
Ichika: Saki and I went to Miku's place again today. We played Untitled, and it took us there.
Ichika: Also, we decided to start a band.
Honami: Oh, just the two of you?
Ichika: Yeah, but you're welcome to join, if you'd like?
Honami: I... I think I'll pass.
Ichika: I figured you'd say that.
Honami: Sorry... I-I was just on my way to buy something. I'd better go.
Ichika: Sure. See you around, Honami.
Honami: *Sigh*...
Honami: How much longer do I have to keep this up?
Honami: .....
Honami: I can't see any stars tonight.
Honami: (Maybe it's because everyone's not with me.)
Ichika: Honami...
Ichika: (Oh no, I forgot the fifth period is math.)
Ichika: (Maybe I can borrow Honami's textbook... Huh?)
Honami: .....
Ichika: (Why is Honami eating her lunch all alone? She normally eats with her friends.)
Ex-Classmate A: Hey, want to go to karaoke after school today? Everyone else is coming.
Ex-Classmate B: Everyone else...but not HER, right?
Ex-Classmate A: Of course not. She's no fun to have around.
Honami: .....
Ichika: Hey, Honami?
Honami: Oh, Ichika...
Ichika: I came to ask if I could borrow your math textbook... But more importantly, are you okay? Did something happen with your friends?
Honami: No, nothing of the sort! I just didn't feel like chatting while eating today, that's all!
Ichika: Are you sure? If something's wrong, you can talk to me.
Honami: It's fine, don't worry about it. It's really nothing.
Ichika: If you say so...
Honami: But...
Honami: Is it really so wrong to care about others?
Ichika: Huh?
Honami: Sorry, I was thinking out loud about something. The next class is starting soon. Here's the math textbook.
Ichika: But what were you saying...
Honami: Don't worry about it. Everything's fine.
Ichika: (After that, whenever I asked her if she was okay, she'd find some excuse to slip away.)
Ichika: (I had my suspicions...)
Ichika: .....
Ichika: If I'd only done something then, maybe things wouldn't have turned out the way they did...
